The 2023 Karnataka Assembly Election was held on May 10, 2023 to elect all 224 members of the Karnataka Legislative Assembly. The Indian National Congress, the Bharatiya Janata Party, and the Janata Dal (Secular) are the main contenders in the election. The election is seen as a referendum on the performance of the BJP government, which has been in power for five years. The voter turnout was 73.19%, the highest ever recorded in the history of elections in Karnataka. The Indian National Congress, the Bharatiya Janata Party, and the Janata Dal (Secular) are all hoping to win the election and form the next government in Karnataka. The election is expected to be closely fought, and it is too early to say who will win.
